==Notes==

* The {{PropertyData|preview_mode}} property is set to {{true}} by default and when the gear is created you'll find this message in the report view: 
*: ''Gear module: Crown gear created, preview_mode = true for improved performance. Set preview_mode property to false when ready to cut teeth.''
* {{PropertyData|module}} (<math>m</math>): Using ISO (International Organization for Standardization) guidelines, Module size is designated as the unit representing gear tooth-sizes. 
** The module multiplied by the number of teeth (<math>m</math>) defines the pitch circle diameter (<math>d</math>): <math>d = m \cdot z</math>
** The module multiplied by Pi (<math>\pi</math>) defines the pitch (<math>p</math>), the arc distance on the pitch circle between corresponding points of adjacent teeth: <math>p = m \cdot \pi</math>
* {{PropertyData|other_teeth}}: Several pinions with the same number of teeth only can be used on one crown wheel.
* {{PropertyData|pressure_angle}}: Only change the parameter, if sufficient knowledge of the gear geometry is available.
* The geometry of the crown gear is primarily determined by the spur pinion geometry according to its number of teeth (thus represented by the {{PropertyData|other_teeth}} property).
* A matching spur gear can be created with [[Image:FCGear_InvoluteGear.svg|16 px]] [[FCGear_InvoluteGear|Involute Gear]]. Its {{PropertyData|num_teeth}} value must equal this crown gear's {{PropertyData|other_teeth}} value.
* Adjustments for optimal running characteristics can be made with the parameters of involute gear.

